M|rules|title: Conditional Module Loading
M|rules|impact: HIGH
M|rules|impactDescription: loads large data only when needed
M|rules|tags: bundle, conditional-loading, lazy-loading
M|rules|Load large data or modules only when a feature is activated.
M|rules|**Example (lazy-load animation frames):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function AnimationPlayer({ enabled, setEnabled }: { enabled: boolean; setEnabled: React.Dispatch<React.SetStateAction<boolean>> }) {
M|rules|const [frames, setFrames] = useState<Frame[] | null>(null)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|if (enabled && !frames && typeof window !== 'undefined') {
M|rules|import('./animation-frames.js')
M|rules|.then(mod => setFrames(mod.frames))
M|rules|.catch(() => setEnabled(false))
M|rules|}
M|rules|}, [enabled, frames, setEnabled])
M|rules|if (!frames) return <Skeleton />
M|rules|return <Canvas frames={frames} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|The `typeof window !== 'undefined'` check prevents bundling this module for SSR, optimizing server bundle size and build speed.